Your argument is wrong. Here is the right bounds:

\begin{align*}
    \frac{dM}{dt} = T(K*A) - M \le 1-M &\implies M(t) \le 1 + (M(0)-1)\,e^{-t} \\
    \frac{dm}{dt} = T(K*A) - m \ge 0-m &\implies m(t) \ge m(0)\,e^{-t} \\
\end{align*}

You can fix your argument by choosing the $N^2$-dimensional cube $\mathcal{B}_\epsilon=[0-\epsilon,1+\epsilon]^{N^2} \subset \mathbb{R}^{N^2}, \epsilon > 0$

is the implication valid?

\begin{align*}
    \frac{dM}{dt} = T(K*A) - M \le 1-M &\implies M(t) \le \max\{1, M(0)e^{-t}\} \\
    \frac{dm}{dt} = T(K*A) - m \ge 0-m &\implies m(t) \ge \min\{0, m(0)e^{-t}\} \\
\end{align*}

\begin{equation}
    \partial_t A(\vec{r},t) = T([K*A](\vec{r},t)) - A(\vec{r},t) \label{asymptotic_lenia}
\end{equation}

Where $A: \mathbb{R}^2 \times \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ is a real-valued scalar field, $K$ is a radially symmetric kernel with sum $1$, $*$ is the convolution operator, and $T: \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}$ is the growth function, applied pointwise. The growth function $T$ is typically a Gaussian function, but is typically approximated via a polynomial or step function for computational efficiency. The PDE is solved on a torus with periodic boundary conditions.

For the above PDE, write an ODE which represents the evolution of a spatially discretized field

Below is the full, index-by-index expression for the discrete cyclic convolution that appears in the ODE.  
Assume the kernel has an odd diameter \(2M+1\) so its discrete coefficients are
\[
K_{u,v},\qquad u,v=-M,\dots ,M, \qquad
\sum_{u=-M}^{M}\sum_{v=-M}^{M} K_{u,v}=1 .
\]

---

### Explicit form at one lattice site  

For a single grid point \((i,j)\) the convolution
\([K*A]_{i,j}\) is

\[
\boxed{
[K*A]_{i,j}
=\!\!\!\!\sum_{u=-M}^{M}\sum_{v=-M}^{M}
      K_{u,v}\;
      A_{\,\bigl(i-u\bigr)\!\!\!\!\pmod{N_x},\;
        \bigl(j-v\bigr)\!\!\!\!\pmod{N_y}}
}
\]

The modulo operation implements the periodic (torus) wrap-around in both directions.

---

### Written out term-by-term (example \(M=1\); a \(3\times3\) kernel)

\[
\begin{aligned}
[K*A]_{i,j} \;=\;
&K_{-1,-1}\,A_{i+1 \pmod{N_x},\, j+1 \pmod{N_y}}
+K_{-1,0}\, A_{i+1 \pmod{N_x},\, j   \pmod{N_y}}
+K_{-1,1}\, A_{i+1 \pmod{N_x},\, j-1 \pmod{N_y}}\\[4pt]
&+K_{0,-1}\, A_{i   \pmod{N_x},\, j+1 \pmod{N_y}}
+K_{0,0}\,  A_{i   \pmod{N_x},\, j   \pmod{N_y}}
+K_{0,1}\,  A_{i   \pmod{N_x},\, j-1 \pmod{N_y}}\\[4pt]
&+K_{1,-1}\,A_{i-1 \pmod{N_x},\, j+1 \pmod{N_y}}
+K_{1,0}\, A_{i-1 \pmod{N_x},\, j   \pmod{N_y}}
+K_{1,1}\, A_{i-1 \pmod{N_x},\, j-1 \pmod{N_y}} .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### Plugging this into the ODE  

With the convolution written explicitly, each lattice value evolves by

\[
\boxed{\;
\frac{d}{dt}A_{i,j}(t)
=\;T\!\Bigl(
\sum_{u=-M}^{M}\sum_{v=-M}^{M}
K_{u,v}\,
A_{(i-u)\!\!\!\!\pmod{N_x},\, (j-v)\!\!\!\!\pmod{N_y}}(t)
\Bigr)\;-\;A_{i,j}(t)\;},
\qquad
i=0,\dots ,N_x\!-\!1,\;
j=0,\dots ,N_y\!-\!1 .
\]

This is the fully explicit, component-wise form of the spatially discretized Lenia-type dynamics.

